@endnode
@node oIsDoubleClick "OpenUtil.library / User Interface / oIsDoubleClick()"

  NAME
        oIsDoubleClick  -- Check for Gadget double-click

  SYNOPSIS
        oIsDoubleClick (ActualGadget, ActualIndex, LastGadget, LastIndex, LastSeconds, LastMicros)
                             D0            D1          A0          A1         A2           A3

        long oIsDoubleClick (struct Gadget *, ULONG, struct Gadget **, ULONG *, ULONG *, ULONG *)

  FUNCTION
        This function is used to see if a Gadget was double-clicked. Beyond the
        intuition DoubleClick() function, this one checks if it was the same
        Gadget and updates all LastGadget and LastTime imformation.

  INPUTS
        ActualGadget    - The Gadget actually clicked, which is found in the
                          current IntuiMessage->IAddress field.

        ActualIndex     - This is used for a special kind of Gadgets (like
                          ListView Gadgets), where it's not enough to know
                          which gadget was clicked the last time. Here you
                          can pass a numeric value, which is, for example,
                          the ordinal number received with the IntuiMessage
                          (IMsg->Code), used with ListView Gadgets. With
                          things like a Button-kind Gadget, an Index value
                          isn't needed, so just pass -1 here.

        LastGadget      - This is a *pointer* to a variable which is declared
                          as a Gadget pointer. LastGadget is updated by
                          oIsDoubleClick() with every call. See example below.

        LastIndex       - Points to a ULONG variable which is updated by
                          oIsDoubleClick(). It holds the last Index value.

        LastSeconds     - Points to a ULONG variable, filled by oIsDoubleClick()
                          each call in order to remember the last time a
                          Gadget was clicked.

        LastMicros      - Like LastSeconds, this one holds the last micro
                          seconds value.

  RESULT
        BOOL            - TRUE, if it was a double-click.

  EXAMPLE

        (Working on a ListView Gadget, else pass -1 for ActualIndex)

        C:
                struct Gadget * myLastGadget   =  0; /* initial values */
                ULONG           myLastIndex    = -1; /*                */
                ULONG           myLastSeconds  =  0; /*                */
                ULONG           myLastMicros   =  0; /*                */

                Result = IsDoubleClick ( (struct Gadget *) IntuiMessage->IAddress,
                                         IntuiMessage->Code,
                                         &myLastGadget,
                                         &myLastIndex,
                                         &myLastSeconds,
                                         &myLastMicros);

        Asm:
                myLastGadget:     dc.l     0
                myLastIndex:      dc.l    -1
                myLastSeconds:    dc.l     0
                myLastMicros:     dc.l     0

                move.l  IntuiMessage,a0
                move.l  IntuiMessage->im_IAddress(a0),d0 ; ActualGadget
                moveq   #0,d1
                move.w  IntuiMessage->im_Code(a0),d1  ; Actual Index
                lea     myLastGadget,a0               ; pointer to LastGadget
                lea     myLastIndex,a1                ; pointer to LastIndex
                lea     myLastSeconds,a2              ; pointer to LastSeconds
                lea     myLastMicros,a3               ; pointer to LastMicros
                jsr     _LVOoIsDoubleClick(a6)
                move.l  d0,Result

  NOTES
        For correct working, initialize LastGadget, LastSeconds & LastMicros
        to NULL and LastIndex to -1 (see example above). As stated before,
        these four variables are updated by oIsDoubleClick.

  AUTHOR
        Oliver "Bloodrock" Lange (bloodrock@bloody.in-berlin.de)
@endnode
