@node oStrCut "OpenUtil.library / String Functions / oStrCut()"

  NAME
        oStrCut -- cut a string at a search string position

  SYNOPSIS
        oStrCut (String, MatchString, MaxRange)
                   A0        A1          D0

        STRPTR oStrCut (STRPTR, STRPTR, ULONG)

  FUNCTION
        Cut a string at the first match with another (part-) match string.
        The part string is searched in the source string; if a match is found,
        the source string gets cut at that position. If nothing was found,
        nothing gets changed. This function is not case-sensitive.

  INPUTS
        String          - The string to truncate

        MatchString     - The string part to search for.

        MaxRange        - the maximum search offset in the source String.

  RESULT
        Result points to the (new) end position of the passed string, no
        matter if the MatchString was found or not. Result always points to
        the trailing NULL byte of the string.

  AUTHOR
        Oliver "Bloodrock" Lange (bloodrock@bloody.in-berlin.de)

  SEE ALSO
        @{" oStrCutCase() " link "oStrCutCase"}, @{" oChrCut() " link "oChrCut"}
@endnode
@node oStrCutCase "OpenUtil.library / String Functions / oStrCutCase()"

  NAME
        oStrCutCase -- cut a string at the first match of another match string

  SYNOPSIS
        oStrCutCase (String, MatchString, MaxRange)
                       A0         A1         D0

        STRPTR oStrCutCase (STRPTR, STRPTR, ULONG)

  FUNCTION
        Cut a string at the first match with another (part-) match string.
        The Cut string is searched in the source string; if a match is found,
        the source string gets cut at that position. If nothing was found,
        nothing gets changed. This function is case-sensitive.

  INPUTS
        String          - The string to truncate.

        MatchString     - The string part to search for.

        MaxRange        - The maximum search offset in the source String.

  RESULT
        Result points to the (new) end position of the passed string, no
        matter if the MatchString was found or not. Result always points to
        the trailing NULL byte of the string.

  AUTHOR
        Oliver "Bloodrock" Lange (bloodrock@bloody.in-berlin.de)

  SEE ALSO
        @{" oStrCut() " link "oStrCut"}, @{" oChrCut() " link "oChrCut"}
@endnode
